{"node_id": "ffff6ebf2a35538a970f009f8b9e2b65", "title": "Summation notation intro", "description": "Evaluate expressions that use sigma notation to make sure you understand what sigma notation means.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "Get ready for AP® Calculus", "Get ready for infinite sequences and series (BC only)", "Summation notation", "Summation notation intro"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "f4052af62ade56a096174d422ea23561", "question_content": "$\\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=1}^{3 }{{(n^2 - 1)}}=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]\n", "hints": ["###What is the question asking for?\n\n$\\sum$ tells us to find the sum.\n\nThe question is asking for the sum of the values of $n^2 - 1$ from $n = 1$ to $n = 3$. \n", "###Evaluating\n\n$\\begin{align} \\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=1}^{3 }{({n^2 - 1})}&= (\\blueD1^2 - 1) + (\\blueD2^2 - 1) + (\\blueD3^2 - 1) \\\\\\\\\n&= 0 + 3 + 8 \\\\\\\\\n&= 11\\end{align}$", "###The answer\n\n$\\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=1}^{3 }{({n^2 - 1})}=11$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 11}]}}}, {"item_id": "4903c8c730a55490a856229191777d28", "question_content": "$\\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=0}^{2 }{{(n)}}=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]\n", "hints": ["###What is the question asking for?\n\n$\\sum$ tells us to find the sum.\n\nThe question is asking for the sum of the values of $n$ from $n = 0$ to $n = 2$. \n", "###Evaluating\n\n$\\begin{align} \\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=0}^{2 }{({n})}&= (\\blueD0) + (\\blueD1) + (\\blueD2) \\\\\\\\\n&= 0 + 1 + 2 \\\\\\\\\n&= 3\\end{align}$", "###The answer\n\n$\\large\\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n=0}^{2 }{({n})}=3$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "si